Title: Surfing for the soul in Portugal
DateModified: '2019-02-01'
DatePublished: '2019-02-01'
Url: https://www.worldnomads.com/create/scholarships/writing/2019/applications/surfing-for-the-soul-in-portugal
SetInCountry: Portugal
Category: A leap into the unknown
AuthorName: Cynthia Wilson
AuthorCountry: United States of America
Text: "A women who is 41 years of age from the US travel to Portugal to meet her long-distance\
  \ lover from Australia of four years. They meet to buy a van and road trip to Spain.\
  \ Every day is spent on the water. He is a kitesurfer, she is learning to surf.\
  \ With every new destination, they learn how surf shaped many of the towns and how\
  \ it can transform the soul in ways unimaginable. \n\nThroughout the story, they\
  \ will dive deep into the culture of Portugal, eat vegetarian and grow deeper in\
  \ their relationship. They have met for six weeks to travel every year for their\
  \ relationship and managed to stay in love. \n\nThis is a story about triumph, learning\
  \ a new sport at 40, adventure and how the heart of the people in Portugal change\
  \ them."
